         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">25/2/67 ¶  ¶ I am not quite well, dear Professor, and can thus only very briefly adress you in response to your very friendly last letters. My indisposition must also be the excuse that I did not send...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">67.02.25a</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Thomas Anderson</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">Royal Botanic Garden Edinburgh, Thos Anderson, box 2, letters from various originators, vol. 1, f. 166.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">25/2/67</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I am not quite well, dear Professor, and can thus only very briefly adress you in response to your very friendly last letters. My indisposition must also be the excuse that I did not send any seeds by this mail. I had a most kind letter from your worthy father<note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Thomas Anderson, secretary of the National bank of Scotland (<seg style="font-style: italic; ">ODNB</seg>). Letter not found.</p>
               </note> and I am so glad that so far the object of our united wishes was accomplished The seeds you so generously supplied have safely arrived I will send you a case with <name key="Araucaria%20Cookii">Araucaria Cookii</name> but have no seeds.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/> I admire your perseverance &amp; success in the Cinchona culture! I have now several thousand plants (the majority C. Condaminea) which I intend this autumn to trust out in our so called "fern tree gullies" Seeds of C. Calisaya &amp; C. micrantha, of which species I have but a limited number are always a great boon</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>We are here in the Australian vegetation excessively poor in <name key="Acanthaceae">Acanthaceae</name>,<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">See Anderson (1864), Anderson (1867).</p>
               </note> even in the north.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">With sincerity</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>your friend</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd Mueller</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
